    gloss "(by extension) Money generally."
    provenance (wiktionary)
  sense
    part_of_speech noun
    gloss "A quarter of a pound or one crown, historically minted as a coin of approximately the same size and composition as a then-contemporary dollar coin of the United States, and worth slightly more."
    provenance (wiktionary)
  sense
    part_of_speech noun
    gloss "Imported from the United States, and paid for in U.S. dollars. (Note: distinguish 'dollar wheat', North American farmers' slogan, meaning a market price of one dollar per bushel.)"
    provenance (wiktionary)
